y adaptations in the latter half of the twentieth century, and early years of the twenty-first century. Although primarily concerned with fiction, the collection includes work on television and film. Authors discussed include Iain Banks, A.S. Byatt, Angela Carter, Simone de Beauvoir, Ted Hughes, Doris Lessing, Ian McEwan Iris Murdoch, Vladimir Nabokov, Andrea Newman and Pier Pasolini and Sylvia Plath.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aIncest in literature. 0aLiterature, Moderny20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aLiterature, Moderny21st centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aSexual abuse victims in literature. 4aGothic 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aContemporary Literature.  aFilm.  aIncest.  aTelevision.  aTrauma, Childhood.1 aBrown, Alistair, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuggan, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGieni, Justine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeeson, Miles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeeson, Miles, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMack, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiller, Emma V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMills, Alice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMundye, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPateman, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPheasant-Kelly, Frances, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWhite, Rebecca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester Universit